gn=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uziann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ziann</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/8/02 5:54:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3740.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> advanced velious faction 301 (+tormax w/o -coldain)</span><hr size=1> this is long and kinda complicated, if you dont like faction tweaking you might not wanna read it, feel free to skip to the questions at the bottom though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br><br><br>i need to get to high amiable with tormax.  i have sneak and a +500 faction song as my tools.  i am now ally yelinak, ally dain, ally coldain, ally zek, scowl tormax/rif (hopefully close to threat), max scowl CoV! ive been ally to every major velious faction at some point in my bardic travels /snicker<br><br><br>recently, i was max kos to all 3 kael factions.  i turned in about 60 coldain heads (bought some and had a ton saved from my dorf slaying days thus retaining coldain/dain faction) and 64 kobold paws to bvellos with sneak.<br>  <br>Im looking for options on raising tormax faction other than dain/yelinak hits (might be a few weeks for those and im impatient) or killing in Icewell.<br><br>When velious first came out i got to amiable tormax after about 100 note/torque to the food vendor guy/ew giant fort quests and a lot of WL mercenary reports. (note: there is a -coldain hit when you bring the note to the giant in EW.)<br>---------------------<br><br>So my questions are these:<br><br>1) Whats the highest non dain/yelinak +tormax faction hit you know of other than killing chamberlain/senchenal in icewell?<br><br>2) Can anyone confirm you need high amiable to get GoDS (ie: if tormax gives you the quest youre gtg)?<br><br>3) Does anyone know the breakdown of positive faction hits from coldain heads/kobold paws to Bvellos (ie: +4 zek, +1 rif/torm, -8 cov for example) or values of any other +tormax hits, or remember the faction levels for kael (ie: -32000 ~ -5000 = scowl, -4999 ~ -1000 = threat, etc)... yes this info prob wouldnt be available to the average player...<br><br>thanks, although the magic 8 ball says odds are slim i will get the answers im looking for <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br>z <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uziann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ziann</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/8/02 5:57:23 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uqalenie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qalenie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/8/02 8:15:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3740.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: advanced velious faction 301 (+tormax w/o -coldain)</span><hr size=1> Only one I can think of offhand is Velketor:<br>[Sun Jan 06 02:54:03 2002] Velketor the Sorcerer has been slain by Bruuss!<br>[Sun Jan 06 02:54:03 2002] Your faction standing with Velketor got worse.<br>[Sun Jan 06 02:54:03 2002] Your faction standing with King Tormax got better.<br><br>I'm told the faction hit isn't very big though.<br><br>Qalenie [59 Conjurer] -= Crimson Twilight =-<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48239">Qalenie's Profile</a> | <a href="http://www.crimsontwilight.org/">Crimson Twilight</a> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubrutultarewmarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brutul Tarew Marr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/8/02 1:04:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3740.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: advanced velious faction 301 (+tormax w/o -coldain)</span><hr size=1> I can confirm that you only need high amiable to turn in GoDS/BoDS.  I have turned in both at high amiable, the Gaunts just Sunday night.  When I hit amiable he said something like &quot;you have proven yourself a a friend to the Kromzek but you have not yet earned my trust&quot;.  At high Amiable he gives you the quest and you're gtg.  <br><br>For raising faction, just farm wolfmasters outside thurg for heads.  I bet I killed 500 of them before I lost ally with Coldain and probably close to 500 more to get down to Amiable.  Sounds like you have dorf faction to burn and the wolfmasters are a tiny hit.  I think it took me 130ish heads and 92 paws to get from high scowls to high amiable with Tormax. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uziann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ziann</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/8/02 2:25:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3740.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> thanks for the feedback =) will keep working on the coldain heads and paws <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uquasinomdeplume.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quasinom de Plume</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.bullhonkie.com/ubb/admin5.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/8/02 5:02:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3740.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> In the mines of coldain are Goos - I've looted coldain heads off them before.  Even though you'll take the hit for handing them in, at least you save some coin and/or faction hits from killing dorfs.  However, they don't drop every time though and there aren't many to kill so it might be quicker to farm HG's for cash to buy the coldain heads heh. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uquasinomdeplume.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quasinom de Plume</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.bullhonkie.com/ubb/admin5.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/8/02 9:28:44 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzania.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zania</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/8/02 6:22:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3740.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> 140 heads, 16paws, dain kill + few quests, and I just got threatening to tormax from max KoS.<br><br>Apparently biggest hits are as follows:<br>Dain / Yelinak<br>Dain's guards<br>4 Paws<br>Coldain heads<br>random quests, like supply delivery<br><br>If you can get a group to help you, I'd say easiest would be to farm Dain's guards, if you cant, welcome to the world of dorf head farming <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Zania<br><br>PS Good thing I dont need ally and just amiable, saves me a lot of dorf farming <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukianwan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kianwan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/8/02 9:01:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3740.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> just kill the bodyguards in EW if you want to get dorf heads without losing coldain faction. You will prolly need someone with harmony to single pull em tho (they are dubious to ALL) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uketocon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ketocon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/9/02 9:52:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3740.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Ive been told Yel takes you from MAX kos to high amiable <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udaedellus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daedellus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/9/02 10:06:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3740.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Possible source of heads without neg coldain hits</span><hr size=1> What about killing dorfs in CC?  They have not had contact with the Coldain since Colin Dain took them from Coldstone.  Dunno if they will give Tormax faction, btu they should drop heads. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3746.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3704.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3740.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3740.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3740.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3740.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3740.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br